---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
        <head>
                <BaseHead title={`Start Here | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="An introduction to Jack Maguire, his philosophy, and his work." />
                <style>
                        .prose h2 {
                                font-size: 1.8em;
                                margin-top: 2em;
                                margin-bottom: 0.5em;
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .prose p {
                                margin-bottom: 1.5em;
                                line-height: 1.8;
                                color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
                        }
                        .prose strong {
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .note {
                                padding: 1.5em;
                                background-color: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.2);
                                border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
                                margin: 2em 0;
                                font-style: italic;
                        }
                </style>
        </head>
        <body>
                <Header />
                <main>
                        <h1>Start Here</h1>
                        <div class="prose">
                                				<p>Welcome to this digital archive. I am Jack Maguire, a performance marketer and writer based in the East Village of New York City. This site is a repository for my writing, technical projects, and firsthand evaluations across paid social media, urbanism, long-distance travel, and gastronomy.</p>

				<h2>Performance Marketing</h2>

				<p>My work as a Senior Paid Social Media Director focuses on scaling campaign structures across Meta, TikTok, and Snapchat. The advertising industry is flooded with noise and vanity metrics. My approach requires deterministic measurement, incrementality testing, and direct attribution. Managing high-volume restaurant operations early in my career taught me how systems function under operational friction. In media buying, I apply these principles by treating creative testing as the primary lever for capital allocation and letting real customer lifetime value dictate budget growth.</p>

				<h2>Urbanism and the East Village</h2>

				<p>Living in the East Village is an active choice driven by an interest in urban planning and spatial economics. Cities thrive when they optimize for density, walkability, and strong local gathering places. Exploring the streets of Manhattan allows me to observe the micro-economies, zoning laws, and daily routines that shape urban life. The constant movement of New York provides a baseline of challenge that encourages resilience and continuous adaptation.</p>

				<h2>Long-Distance Travel</h2>

				<p>Travel functions as a project in logistics and calculated risk. Navigating remote four-wheel-drive tracks in the Australian Outback or planning complex overland routes through South America requires analytical preparation. I design itineraries using minimalist principles to reduce friction and increase focus. Thru-hiking the Appalachian Trail in ninety-nine days established a high benchmark for physical endurance. Solo travel requires intentional structure, where shared accommodations and local transport operate as tools to balance personal autonomy with deep community immersion.</p>

				<h2>Gastronomy</h2>

				<p>Food represents a intersection of local culture, agriculture, and culinary science. My interest covers everything from the chemistry of high-heat cooking to the logistics of fast-casual operations. Evaluating a high-end tasting menu or a local pizza slice requires the same standard: clean execution, high-quality ingredients, and a clear point of view from the kitchen.</p>

				<h2>Philosophy of Presence</h2>

				<p>My intellectual interests focus on existentialism and phenomenology. Attempting to treat grief or personal setbacks as simple optimization problems fails. Meaning does not occur through automated systems; it accumulates through small, authentic experiences: a quiet conversation, a shared meal, or a demanding text. I focus on being present rather than hyper-optimizing every hour, maintaining an honest assessment of both my setbacks and my structural achievements in statistics, philosophy, and modern software tools.</p>

				<h2>Social Connection</h2>

				<p>Hosting, connecting, and bringing people together form the core of my social life. I value the energy of live music and electronic music culture, but I recognize that social utility differs from genuine connection. I prioritize friendships built on shared vulnerability, intellectual honesty, and mutual respect, which require a life that is fully inhabited and engaged.</p>

				<h2>Synthesis</h2>

				<p>The essays on this site aim to clarify complex topics through direct, objective prose. By understanding how incentives, networks, and physical realities function, we can build cleaner models of the world. This page is an active document tracking my research on media measurement, urban geography, and the search for authentic experience.</p>
                        </div>
                </main>
                <Footer />
        </body>
</html>
